      <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/ForRedundantSystemsCheckThatEachSte-0FD805BD"
            class="- topic/note ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems: </b> Check that each step is perform on
both units before proceeding to next step.</note>
      <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/ForDualSystemsPerformAllTheStepsOnO-0FD807C7"
            otherprops="typeD"
            class="- topic/note ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems: </b>Perform all the steps
on one unit, then repeat the complete procedure for the other unit.</note>
      <note platform="WxW" type="important" class="- topic/note "> The DC capacitors needs to
be charged before the inverter input switch is closed.</note>
      <ol class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system is turned off.</p>
         </li>
         <li otherprops="generalM 2pMBS 3pMBS"
             platform="PxW WxW"
             class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for systems with a manual bypass switch: </b>Make sure the manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> position. If
not turn the manual bypass switch(es) to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> position.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier mains breaker to turn
on the power supply to the rectifier.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the external source of the DC input
power is available.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch it in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the inverter input switch. If not possible, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the inverter input switch.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">After about 10 seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
            <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                  class="- topic/note "/>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second, if the unit did
not start from the autostart. After a few seconds or if any key is
pressed the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal
operation load power ...%</codeph>
               <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge
load ...%</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the
DC voltage.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">If the DC voltage is within tolerance, close
the battery breaker and battery protection breaker if applicable.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b> to check that
the inverter output voltage is within the tolerance range.</p>
         </li>
         <li otherprops="generalM 2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS"
             platform="PxW WxW"
             class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for systems with a bypass: </b>Close
the bypass mains breaker to connect the bypass.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
